  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6763.63 sitting just above the max negative gamma strike at 6760 (-17.2B), dealers are in active buying mode to hedge their short gamma exposure, providing tactical support but creating whipsaw conditions. The massive negative GEX wall cluster between 6750-6770 creates a dangerous amplification zone where any directional move will be accelerated by dealer flow - breaks below 6760 trigger more dealer buying while moves toward 6780 (max positive gamma) face increasing dealer selling pressure. The recent GEX surge detection combined with BREAKOUT regime confirms we're in a high-volatility environment where dealer hedging will amplify rather than dampen price swings.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect wild swings with support around 6760 but any break lower gets amplified fast.",
